SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 2810
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE VOSS.
6264H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 160, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to youth
organizations providing information, services, and activities to students within school
districts.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 160, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 160.3400, to read as follows:
160.3400. 1. As used in this section, the following terms mean:
2 (1) "School", the same meaning as defined in section 160.077;
3 (2) "School district", the same meaning as defined in section 160.011;
4 (3) "Youth organization", a corporation chartered by Congress and listed in
5 Title 36, Subtitle II, Part B, as of January 1, 2026.
6 2. (1) Each school district shall, upon request, allow a representative of any
7 youth organization to provide:
8 (a) Oral or written information to the students of such school district regarding
9 the youth organization and how such youth organization furthers the educational
10 interests and civic involvement of students in a manner consistent with good citizenship;
11 and
12 (b) Services and activities to any student of such school district who is a member
13 of such youth organization.
14 (2) Each requesting youth organization shall be permitted to provide such
15 information, services, and activities in a school building or on the school grounds of a
16 school in each school district at least once during each school year.
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

HB 2810 2
17 3. Each school district shall make a good-faith effort to select a date, time, and
18 location for each requesting youth organization to provide such information, services, or
19 activities that is mutually agreeable to the school district and to the youth organization.
20 Oral information provided under paragraph (a) of subdivision (1) of subsection 2 of this
21 section shall be provided only during noninstructional time.
22 4. Prior to allowing a representative of a youth organization to provide
23 information, services, or activities at a school under this section, such representative
24 shall be subject to a background check. Except as otherwise provided by this section or
25 by procedures set forth by the Missouri state highway patrol, the parameters of the
26 background check shall be determined by the relevant school district. A school district
27 may prohibit any representative of a youth organization who has been convicted of a
28 felony from providing information, services, or activities under this section at any school
29 in such school district. Each representative of a youth organization is responsible for all
30 costs associated with obtaining such background check.
